# Fitting Generalized Additive Models (GAMs) for Non-linear
# Home Price is the dependent variable and 'neighborhood_factors' are predictors
gam_formula <- as.formula(
  paste("HomePrice ~", paste(paste0("s(", neighborhood_factors, ")"), collapse = " + "))
)

# Fit the GAM model
gam_model <- gam(gam_formula, data = data)

Gradient the Algorithms

x=data[c("CrimeRate","IndustrialZone","Distance","Rooms","PupilTeacherRatio")]
y=data$HomePrice

Standardize the residual

zscore <- function(x, mean.val=NA) {
if(is.matrix(x)) return(apply(x, 2, zscore, mean.val=mean.val))
if(is.data.frame(x)) return(data.frame(apply(x, 2, zscore, mean.val=mean.val)))

if(is.na(mean.val)) mean.val <- mean(x)
sd.val <- sd(x)
if(all(sd.val == 0)) return(x) # if all the values are the same
(x - mean.val) / sd.val
}
# Standardize the features
x.scaled <- zscore(x)
data$CrimeRate <- x.scaled$CrimeRate
data$IndustrialZone <- x.scaled$IndustrialZone
data$Distance <-  x.scaled$Distance
data$Rooms <- x.scaled$Rooms
data$PupilTeacherRatio <- x.scaled$PupilTeacherRatio

The Algorithm

num.iterations = 1000

# Gradient descent function
grad <- function(x, y, theta) {
gradient <- (1 / nrow(y)) * (t(x) %*% (1/(1 + exp(-x %*% t(theta))) - y))
return(t(gradient))
}
gradient.descent <- function(x, y, alpha=0.1, num.iterations = 1000, threshold=1e-5,
output.path=FALSE) {
# Add x_0 = 1 as the first column
m <- if(is.vector(x)) length(x) else nrow(x)
if(is.vector(x) || (!all(x[,1] == 1))) x <- cbind(rep(1, m), x)
if(is.vector(y)) y <- matrix(y)
x <- apply(x, 2, as.numeric)
num.features <- ncol(x)
# Initialize the parameters
theta <- matrix(rep(0, num.features), nrow=1)
# Look at the values over each iteration
theta.path <- theta
for (i in 1:num.iterations) {
theta <- theta - alpha * grad(x, y, theta)
if(all(is.na(theta))) break
theta.path <- rbind(theta.path, theta)
if(i > 2) if(all(abs(theta - theta.path[i-1,]) < threshold)) break
}
if(output.path) return(theta.path) else return(theta.path[nrow(theta.path),])
}

#Check the results

theta.hat.each.ite <- gradient.descent(x=x.scaled, y=y, num.iterations=num.iterations, output.path=TRUE)

#Estimated results

theta.hat.each.ite[nrow(theta.hat.each.ite),]
